Nathan,

Oh very yes, and very black humor, indeed.  I enjoyed it very much.

I just happened to be reading the story on the young Missouri mom when your 
original post came through and wasn't sure if it had reached the 
international level. I also recalled the little incident over the 'Ninja 
Day' thing.  Such disconnects with reality and inability to discern fact 
from fiction & satire is very scary to me.

But don't get me written off as a sour old she-goat who wants nothing more 
than to head-butt everything in sight. I'm very ready to laugh at the 
foibles of humans (including myself), be silly, play with my kids, sing 
off-key, and render a very sharp opinion once in a while..... among other 
things....

.... don't forget, wicked, too....

Lizzie
